{
  "texts": [
    "In section 3.3, we will choose to work in a picture where Y0 = 0, such that upon setting Z0 = 0, we have U0 = V0 = 0.",
    "We are working in picture P = -2, so the full physical state is really [|Φw⟩] σ w e 2ρ+iσ+iH.",
    "Since J + and J 3 do not commute, V w m 1,m 2 (x; z) has definite values for x and j = m1 -m2 but is not a state of definite m = m1 + m2.",
    "We thank Kiarash Naderi for pointing this out to us.",
    "Further details may be found in appendix B. Whilst our focus will be on the ground states here, we note that the generalisation to include the DDF operators of[15] is not straightforward as they have non-trivial ghost dependence."
  ]
}